# Instinct RPG — Primer chargen sample keys

The live primer mounts one Baserow card per chargen step via the `MOUNTS` object in
`instinct-rpg-primer-v2.html`. **Do not hand-paste card HTML** — always pull from `card-data.js`.

## Current mounts (keep in sync with the file)

| DOM id | Card_Key | Chargen step |
|--------|----------|--------------|
| `instinct-card-wrap` | `bold-instinct` | 5 Instincts |
| `bond-card-wrap` | `warm-presence-bond` | 1 Bond |
| `connection-card-wrap` | `connection-template` | 1 Connection |
| `background-card-wrap` | `field-medic-background` | 1 Background |
| `ancestry-card-wrap` | `human-ancestry` | 1 Ancestry |
| `item-card-wrap` | `immovable-rod-item` | 1 Item |
| `core-card-wrap-a` | `weapon-master-fighter-core` | Class Core (sample 1) |
| `core-card-wrap-b` | `battlemaster-fighter-core` | Class Core (sample 2) |
| `ability-card-wrap` | `find-the-gap-rogue` | 12 Abilities (sample) |
| `walkthrough-card-wrap` | `break-barbarian` | §3 check walkthrough (Break) |

When you change a key in the primer script, **update this table** in the same commit.

## Swapping a sample

1. Pick a replacement from `card-data.js` with `Status: current` and the right card type/class.
2. Update the `MOUNTS` entry (and HTML `id` only if the wrap element is renamed).
3. Confirm the card renders in the primer — check `instinct-primer-card-parity.mdc` if the template
   differs (Core vs `.cbody` vs `.bf-body`).
4. Prefer cards that **teach the type** clearly (readable at primer scale, representative anatomy).
5. Commit + push; no Baserow push unless you also changed card HTML in Baserow.

## Regenerating `card-data.js`

If Baserow card HTML changed during the session, regenerate `card-data.js` per
`instinct-agent-ops.mdc` / `at-session-close` step 3b — samples read live data on page load.

